    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_arazyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>arazyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>aræzt</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>arazun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>arazt</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>направлять</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>direct</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сооружать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>construct</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>строить</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>build</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>делать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>make</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>отделывать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>put the final touches on</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>наряжать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>decorate</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <sense xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>сажать (семена, растение)</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>plant (seeds, a plant)</q>
                    </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">также</note><note type="comment"
                        xml:lang="en">also</note></sense>
                <re xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                    <lang/>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>araznæ</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>руль</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>steering wheel</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>fælors kʼoxæj æ zærdæmæ isarazta i cirǧ kard</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>бледной рукой к своему сердцу она направила острый меч</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>she pointed a sharp sword towards her heart with a pale hand</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Batraz... zaǧta topʒyjæn: „Xorz mæ saraz Tynty kalakmæ æmæ mæ
                            fexs“</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Батраз сказал пушкарю: «Хорошенько направь меня на город Тынт и
                                выстрели меня»</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Batraz said to the gunner: “Direct me well to the city of Tynt and
                                shoot me”</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dwarmæ saræztoj sæ nyx</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>устремились („направили лоб“) к воротам</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they rushed ("directed their forehead") to the gate</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>39</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Batraz jæ kʼæxtæ saræzta zæppaʒmæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Батраз уперся ногами в склеп</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Batraz set his feet against the crypt</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 26</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xæʒar ḱī næ saræzta, ūj autæ %i(sic!)%i ænqæly cæǵynʒtæ bynæj
                            yssydysty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кто не строил дома, думает, что столбы выросли из земли</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>those who did not build houses think that the pillars grew out of the
                                ground</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>sarazut myn ḱyryn æmæ mæ ūm nyværūt æmæ mæ denǧyzy bapparūt</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сделайте мне ковчег, положите меня в него и киньте меня в море</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>make me an ark, put me in it and throw me into the sea</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>isarazta e næwæg æfsædtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>снарядил он новое войско</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he equipped a new army</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/><biblScope>110</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>læpputæ sæxi saræztoj æmæ ašydysty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>юноши нарядились и пошли (добывать жен)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>young men dressed up and went (to get wives)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            56</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>max ba araztan kartof</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мы сажали картофель</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>we planted potatoes</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>I 65</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к *%iārāz%i-. Старое сращение преверба %ia%i- с
                    %iraz%i- (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*reǵ-</w></mentioned>) ‘направлять’ и пр. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>razk kun</w>
                        <gloss><q>строить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>починять</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>razk</w>
                        <gloss><q>прямой</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><lang/>
                        <w>vi-raz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>направлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сооружать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>делать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>приводить в порядок</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope
                                    xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр. 27, 136 сл.,
                                    273</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p. 27,
                                    136 ff., 273</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope
                                    xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр. 27, 136 сл.,
                                    273</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p. 27,
                                    136 ff., 273</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>rēz- : rāst</w>
                        <gloss><q>делать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>строить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>готовить</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"
                                    /><biblScope>I 285</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I
                                285</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>pat-raz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>püt-rüz</w>
                        <gloss><q>вытягиваться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>стоять прямо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>afraz-(afrāxtan)</w>
                        <gloss><q>возвышать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>подымать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>rāz</w>
                        <gloss><q>строение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>строитель</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>архитектор</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>murarius</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Vullers"/><biblScope>II
                                    4</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Vullers"/><biblScope>II
                                    4</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>rāz</w>
                        <gloss><q>строение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>строитель</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                                    (<bibl><author>Geiger</author><biblScope>Arch. Orient. 1938 X
                                    210</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Henning</author><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX
                                87</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><author>Geiger</author><biblScope>Arch. Orient. 1938 X
                                    210</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Henning</author><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX
                                87</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>rrāys-(=rāz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>направлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>harays-(=ha-raz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>протягивать(ся)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>birays(=bi-raz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>простираться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>raz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>rāz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>направлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>raj-(irajyati)</w>
                        <gloss><q>направлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>управлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>όρέγω</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>rego</w>
                        <gloss><q>направлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>управлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>richten</w>
                        <gloss><q>направлять</q></gloss></mentioned>. В составе некоторых скифских
                    собственных имен можно предполагать наличие этого глагола: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Φανδάραζος</w></mentioned> (ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fænd"/>
                    ‘замысел’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arazyn"/>, см.: <bibl><author>Вс.
                            Миллер</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope
                            xml:lang="ru">1886, окт., стр. 256 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">1886, oct., p. 256 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Vasmer._Ir._i._S."
                        /><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>). Сильный вид основы без преверба
                    (*%irazyn%i) в осетинском не сохранился, но ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_rast"/> ‘прямой’ представляет старое прош. причастие от этого
                    глагола; см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_færazyn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 82</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>.-— <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>I 62, 178, 227,
                            574</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to *%iārāz%i-. An old fusion of the preverb
                    %ia%i- with %iraz%i- (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*reǵ-</w></mentioned>) ‘direct’ etc. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>razk kun</w>
                        <gloss><q>build</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>repair</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>razk</w>
                        <gloss><q>straight</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><lang/>
                        <w>vi-raz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>direct</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>erect</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>make</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>arrange</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt.
                                    III, Bd. IV, стр. 27, 136 сл., 273</biblScope><biblScope
                                    xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p. 27, 136 ff.,
                                273</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope
                                    xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр. 27, 136 сл.,
                                    273</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p. 27,
                                    136 ff., 273</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>rēz- : rāst</w>
                        <gloss><q>make</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>build</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>prepare</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I
                                    285</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"
                            > (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"
                                    /><biblScope>I 285</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>pat-raz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>püt-rüz</w>
                        <gloss><q>stretch</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>stand straight</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>afraz-(afrāxtan)</w>
                        <gloss><q>erect</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>raise</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>rāz</w>
                        <gloss><q>building</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>builder</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>architect</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>murarius</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Vullers"/><biblScope>II
                                    4</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Vullers"/><biblScope>II
                                    4</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>rāz</w>
                        <gloss><q>building</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>builder</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                                    (<bibl><author>Geiger</author><biblScope>Arch. Orient. 1938 X
                                    210</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Henning</author><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX
                                87</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><author>Geiger</author><biblScope>Arch. Orient. 1938 X
                                    210</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Henning</author><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX
                                87</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>rrāys-(=rāz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>direct</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>harays-(=ha-raz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>stretch (oneself)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><w>birays(=bi-raz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>extend</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>raz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>rāz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>direct</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>raj-(irajyati)</w>
                        <gloss><q>direct</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>rule</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>όρέγω</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>rego</w>
                        <gloss><q>direct</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>rule</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>richten</w>
                        <gloss><q>direct</q></gloss></mentioned>. One can assume the presence of
                    this verb as a part of some Scythian proper names: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Φανδάραζος</w></mentioned> (Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fænd"/>
                    ‘intension’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arazyn"/>, see: <bibl><author>Вс.
                            Миллер</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope
                            xml:lang="ru">1886, окт., стр. 256 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">1886, oct., p. 256 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Vasmer._Ir._i._S."
                        /><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>). A strong variant of the stem without
                    preverb (*%irazyn%i) is lost in Ossetic, but Ossetic <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_rast"/> ‘straight’ is an old past participle of this verb;
                    see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_færazyn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 82</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>.-— <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>I 62, 178, 227,
                            574</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
        </body>
    </text>
